Three male examples from Chiriqui, agreeing with others from Brazil. No mention is made by Boheman of the sexual differences, the males having, as in some of the allied formS, the elytra very obtuse and almost separately rounded at the apex. The antennae are moderately elongate and subfiliform, with joint 3 much shorter and thinner than 2, 4 twice as long as 3, 5 nearly twice as long as 4, 6-10 subequal in length, 11 very elongate, black at the tip.
